      <section eId="sec_CCP-3335">
        <num>CCP 3335</num>
        <heading>3335. Notice to heirs and residuary legatees</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3335__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A copy of any account filed by a succession representative shall be served
upon each heir or residuary legatee, together with a notice that the account may be
homologated after the expiration of ten days from the date of service and that any
opposition thereto shall be filed before homologation.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3335__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the case of any account other than the final account, service on either
a resident or a nonresident may be made by ordinary mail.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3335__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the case of a final account, service may be made by either of the
following:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-3335__subsec_C__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>In accordance with the provisions of Article 1314.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-3335__subsec_C__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>On either a resident or a nonresident, by certified mail or by use of a
commercial courier that requires a signed receipt from the addressee upon completion
of delivery.  The certificate of the attorney for the succession representative that the
notice and final account were sent to the heir or legatee, together with the receipt
signed by the addressee, shall be filed in the succession proceeding prior to
homologation of the final account.
Amended by</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111720</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
